 ORANGE BOOK, THE n. The U.S. Government's standards document (Trusted
Computer System Evaluation Criteria, DOD standard 5200.28-STD, December,
1985) characterizing secure computing architectures, defining levels A1 (most
secure) through C3 (least). Stock UNIXes are roughly C2. see also RED BOOK,
BLUE BOOK, GREEN BOOK, SILVER BOOK, PURPLE BOOK, WHITE BOOK, PINK-SHIRT BOOK,
DRAGON BOOK.